The ciphertext in `shipping_address_encrypted` decrypts to a JSON object conforming to:

```json
{
  "line1":       "string, required",
  "line2":       "string | null",
  "city":        "string, required",
  "region":      "string | null",
  "postal_code": "string, required",
  "country":     "string, required — ISO 3166-1 alpha-2"
}
```

### 4.5 Validation Rules

| Field | Rule |
|---|---|
| `order_id` | UUID v4 format; immutable once set |
| `order_number` | Regex: `^ORD-\d{8}-\d{6}$` |
| `status` | Must be a valid `OrderStatus` symbol; transition must follow the allowed state machine (see §4.6) |
| `version` | Must be strictly greater than the last-seen version for this `order_id` |
| `currency` | ISO 4217; must match across all financial fields in the same event |
| `total_minor_units` | Must equal `subtotal + tax + shipping - discount`; reject if not |
| `line_items` | Array length ≥ 1; each `line_total = quantity × unit_price - discount` |
| `quantity` | Integer ≥ 1 |
| `tax_rate_basis_points` | Integer 0–10000 |
| `customer_email_encrypted` | If non-null, must be valid Vault Transit ciphertext (prefix `vault:v1:`) |
| `locale` | BCP 47 regex: `^[a-z]{2}(-[A-Z]{2})?$` |
| `metadata` keys | Regex: `^[a-z0-9_-]+:[a-z0-9_-]+$` (namespaced) |
| `idempotency_key` | Format: `{producer_service}:{order_id}:{event_type}:{occurred_at_epoch_ms}` |

